2014-05-17 commit r4146 Greg Beam <ki7mt@yahoo.com>

* Fixed typo's in configure.ac + minor edits
* Minor edits & updates to wspr-dist.sh
* Added make dist: target to Makfile.in

  Requires: bash and readlink

  [USAGE]
  ./autogen.sh
  make dist
  
  Creates: ../wspr/dist/WSPR-4.0-linux.tar.gz
  
  Name and version are taken from @PROGRAM@ and @VERSION@, which is
  set in configure.ac header. If you want to change the filename,
  call the script directly from a shell.

  Note: After running make dist, you will need to run
  autogen.sh again, as make dist performs a distclean before
  building the tar.gz file, just in case something slips by.
  
  
2014-05-17 commit r4145 Greg Beam <ki7mt@yahoo.com>

